abstract: After months of political wrangling, House Democrats agreed Tuesday to President Donald Trump’s revamped version of a 25-year-old North American free trade agreement. But they pried some concessions out of the Trump administration before saying they’d go along.
snippet: After months of political wrangling, House Democrats agreed Tuesday to President Donald Trump’s revamped version of a 25-year-old North American free trade agreement. But they pried some concessions out of the Trump administration before saying th...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After months of political wrangling, House Democrats agreed Tuesday to President Donald Trump’s revamped version of a 25-year-old North American free trade agreement. But they pried some concessions out of the Trump administration before saying they’d go along.
headline_main: Democrats Agree to North America Trade Pact: What's in It?
headline_print_headline: Democrats Agree to North America Trade Pact: What's in It?

abstract: A senior Interior Department official broke  ethics rules when he met with his former employer to discuss Interior business, the inspector general said.
snippet: A senior Interior Department official broke  ethics rules when he met with his former employer to discuss Interior business, the inspector general said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — A top Interior Department official broke a federal ethics rule by improperly meeting with his former employer, a conservative research organization, to discuss the rollback of endangered species protections that the group had been pushing, the department’s internal watchdog said in a report published Tuesday.
